11/06/2006
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer is expected to pay a visit to Skopje on Monday (12 June), according to a press statement from the Alliance's headquarters in Brussels. He is scheduled to meet with Macedonian President Branko Crvenkovski, Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski, Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva and Defence Minister Jovan Manasievski.
In other news, the Macedonian Army announced on Saturday that a 17-member helicopter team would be deployed in BiH for a six-month peacekeeping mission as part of the EU operation Althea on 15 July. The Macedonian peacekeepers will serve under Belgian command in Mostar. (A1 TV - 10/06/06; NATO Web site - 09/06/06)
